    <section id="fs-id2605865" class="section-summary"><title>Section Summary</title><list id="import-auto-id2694245"><item id="import-auto-id2694247">Electric potential is potential energy per unit charge.<emphasis effect="bold"/></item>
    <item id="import-auto-id2694252">The potential difference between points A and B, <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>V</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>B</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">–</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>V</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>A</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>, defined to be the change in potential energy of a charge <emphasis effect="italics"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>q</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math></emphasis> moved from A to B, is equal to the change in potential energy divided by the charge, Potential difference is commonly called voltage, represented by the symbol
<m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>Δ</m:mtext><m:mi>V</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>.<equation id="eip-id1820754"><m:math>
        
          <m:mrow>

              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow><m:mn>Δ</m:mn>
                    <m:mi fontstyle="italic">V </m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                    <m:mfrac>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mtext>ΔPE</m:mtext>
                      </m:mrow>
                      <m:mi>q</m:mi>
                    </m:mfrac>
                  </m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/>
                  <m:mtext>and ΔPE = </m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.25em"/>
                  <m:mi fontstyle="italic">q</m:mi><m:mn>Δ</m:mn><m:mi fontstyle="italic">V</m:mi>
                  <m:mtext>.</m:mtext>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>

            <m:mrow/>
          </m:mrow>
          
        
      </m:math>

    </equation></item>

    <item id="import-auto-id2555666">An electron volt is the energy given to a fundamental charge accelerated through a potential difference of 1 V. In equation form,
    <equation id="eip-998"><m:math>
        
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mtable columnalign="left">
                <m:mtr><m:mtd><m:mtext>1 eV</m:mtext></m:mtd>
<m:mtd>                            <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo></m:mtd>
<m:mtd>
                 
                          <m:mfenced open="(" close=")">
                            <m:mrow>
                              <m:mn>1.60</m:mn>
                              <m:mo>×</m:mo>
                              <m:msup>
                                <m:mtext>10</m:mtext>
                                      <m:mtext>–19</m:mtext>
                              </m:msup><m:mspace width="0.25em"/>
                              <m:mtext> C</m:mtext>
                            </m:mrow>
                          </m:mfenced>
                            <m:mfenced open="(" close=")">
                                <m:mn>1 V</m:mn>
                            </m:mfenced>

                            <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                          </m:mtd></m:mtr>
                          <m:mtr><m:mtd/><m:mtd>

                            <m:mfenced open="(" close=")">
                              <m:mrow>
                                <m:mn>1.60</m:mn>
                                <m:mi>×</m:mi>
                                <m:msup>
                                  <m:mtext>10</m:mtext>
                                        <m:mtext>–19</m:mtext>
                                </m:msup><m:mspace width="0.25em"/>
                                <m:mtext>C</m:mtext>
                              </m:mrow>
                            </m:mfenced>
                            <m:mfenced open="(" close=")">
                              <m:mrow>
                                <m:mn>1 J/C</m:mn>
                              </m:mrow>
                            </m:mfenced>
                       </m:mtd>
                </m:mtr>
                <m:mtr><m:mtd/>
<m:mtd>
                            <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo></m:mtd>
<m:mtd>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>1.60</m:mn>
                    <m:mo>×</m:mo>
                    <m:msup>
                      <m:mtext>10</m:mtext>
                            <m:mtext>–19</m:mtext>
                    </m:msup><m:mspace width="0.25em"/>
                    <m:mtext> J.</m:mtext>
                  </m:mrow></m:mtd>
                </m:mtr>
              </m:mtable>
            </m:mrow>
          </m:mrow>
        
      </m:math> </equation></item>
    <item>Mechanical energy is the sum of the kinetic energy and potential energy of a system, that is, <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>KE</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo><m:mtext>PE</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:math> This sum is a constant.</item>
</list></section><section id="fs-id2660778" type="conceptual-questions" class="conceptual-questions"><title>Conceptual Questions</title>
